Prompt 1: Core Layout & iOS-Style Navigation
Intent: Generate the foundational UI shell and navigation.
Prompt: "Act as an expert frontend engineer. Create a mobile-first, iOS-style web application layout using strictly vanilla HTML, JS, and Tailwind CSS (via CDN). Include a bottom tab bar with 5 icons (Summary, Live Gym, Matrix, Coaches, Plan) using Lucide Icons. Implement a smooth view-switching logic in JavaScript so only one main view is visible at a time. The overall theme should be dark mode (background color #000000) with glassmorphism effects (backdrop-blur)."

Prompt 2: Body Recomposition Matrix & Charts
Intent: Build the core logic for the body calibration matrix.
Prompt: "Create a 3x3 grid component for selecting body types (ranging from Slender/Lean to High Mass/Stocky). When a user selects a 'Baseline' and a 'Target', calculate a workout split (ratio of strength training to cardio). Use Chart.js to dynamically render these results into two charts: a doughnut chart for the 'Macro Split' and a bar chart for the 'System Focus' (Z1, Z2, HIIT, METCON). Provide separate theme colors for Male (Blue) and Female (Pink) modes."

Prompt 3: Coach Booking System
Intent: Generate the coach listing and scheduling interface.
Prompt: "Design a coach booking interface. First, display a list of coaches with their avatar, name, and specialty tags. When a coach is clicked, transition to a detail view containing a horizontal scrollable calendar showing the dates for the next 7 days. When a date is clicked, reveal a scrollable schedule grid. Add logic to handle 'Booking' and 'Canceling' sessions, updating the state in localStorage and reflecting the booked status on the home dashboard."

Prompt 4: Full-Screen Workout Timer
Intent: Add an immersive workout tracking feature.
Prompt: "Build a full-screen, immersive workout timer overlay, hidden by default (z-index 100). When triggered via the JavaScript function startWorkoutTimer(category, title, color), make the overlay visible. It should display a large pulsing ring, the elapsed time (MM:SS), and a 'Finish' button. When 'Finish' is clicked, log the elapsed minutes to a global state variable and hide the overlay."
